      "text": "Dark patterns are not accidents. They are designed — often by skilled practitioners working within incentive structures that reward engagement over wellbeing. This paper taxonomises the most common manipulation techniques, traces their psychological mechanisms, and examines the designer's culpability and room to resist within organisational contexts.",
